<br>
I know it's tough bog.. even as a shaman i have a hard time getting a group for the trials because our slows are practically useless and we can't heal during the exec fight. (well we can, heh but i am assuming it would be interesting)<br>
<br>
all we are good for are buffs, and damage.. but druids have better DD's then us, our DoTs albiet a good idea won't do the damage that is required in the 30 seconds to kill the mob before the prisoner gets his head cut off.<br>
<br>
I do like the trials tho.. AND i do like the fact that it requires skill to get into PoV/S. I look at it this way, Verant gave us a zone where we don't have to deal with the average ebayed b00b LFG that is going to get our group killed within 20 seconds. <br>
<br>
I am thankful for that. As for the other classes, it's doable.. you mentioned 5 slots.. the 6th can be for SK's, Pallys, mages, druids, shaman, etc etc etc.. <br>
<br>
I suggest that you get 4 friends together, a cleric, a tank w/AE taunt, a wizard and someone w/high dps (wizard, rogue, monk) and go do the trials. Pick up an extra person and have a go..<br>
